# bubble-sim

LLM-agent simulation framework for bubble game experiments.

## Purpose
The purpose of this project is to simulate and experiment with LLM-based agents in a bubble-game environment.

## Scope
- LLM-agent behavior simulation.
- Environment modeling for bubble games.
- Metrics and evaluation of agent performance.

## Setup
```bash
make install
```

## Repo Structure
- `src/bubble_sim`: Main package.
- `tests`: Unit and integration tests.
- `configs`: Configuration files.
- `scripts`: Utility scripts.

## Development Commands
- `make format`: Format code with Black and Ruff.
- `make lint`: Run linting checks.
- `make test`: Run tests with pytest.
- `make check`: Run all linting and tests.

## Roadmap
- Phase 0.1: Repo setup and standards (current).
- Phase 0.2: Core environment logic.
- Phase 0.3: LLM agent integration.
